<P>AN ESSAY ON THE RHUS TOXICODENDRON, <HI>PUBESCENT POISON OAK,</HI> OR SUMACH, WITH CASES SHEWING IT'S EFFICACY IN THE CURE OF PARALYSIS, AND OTHER DISEASES OF EXTREME DEBILITY.</P>
<P>BY <HI>JOHN ALDERSON,</HI> M. D.</P>
<P>Member of the Ro<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">al Medical Society, EDINBURGH;</P>
<P>&mdash; Philo&s;ophical and Literary Society, NEWCASTLE</P>
<P>And Phy&s;ician to the General Infirmary at HULL.</P>
